Package uk.ac.rhul.cs2800

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Calculator
    A calculator interface for the Reverse Polish Calculator and Infix Calculator.
    Observer
    A functional interface for creating Observers.
    ViewInterface
    View Interface allows calculation of string expressions.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AsciiView
    The ASCIIView allows for Console use of the Calculator.
    CalcController
    CalcController creates views and models.
    CalcModel
    A CalcModel is created to decouple GUIView and ASCIIView.
    Driver
    The Driver class creates some objects and makes them work nicely, then begins the program.
    Entry
    This class processes input into their different types.
    GuiView
    A graphical window with a text friend for expression, a calculate button and a radio button for determining notation.
    NumStack
    A facade to hide details.
    OpStack
    Implements a stack of symbols.
    RevPolishCalc
    Evaluates Reverse Polish String Expressions.
    Stack
    The Stack class that will store Calculator Entries.
    StandardCalc
    Evaluates infix string expressions.
    StrStack
    The Shunting algorithm requires reversing an expression in order to evaluate left to right - so we provide a facade to hide details.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Symbol
    The Symbol Enumerated types allow us to differentiate the character / operator being input.
    Type
    Enumerated Types to discern the type of input.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    BadTypeException
    BadTypeException called when an Entry is resolved to the wrong type.
    InvalidExpression
    InvalidExpression exception for invalid expressions.
